This paper deals with the construction of wait-free multireader shared registers, which are fundamental objects in concurrent computation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves data structures and algorithms, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely category. The construction of shared registers involves the use of control bits, which relates to cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also deals with timestamp-based constructions, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the optimization of time complexity, which relates to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
